description2: Julia Zemiro takes Kerry O'Brien back to his childhood in Brisbane. He speaks candidly about his difficult relationship with the Brothers at St Laurence's College and the long-term effects of a journalism career.

title: Laura's Choice
description: Laura Henkel is eccentric, outspoken, feisty and 90 years old. She has decided she wants to end her life on her own terms, and she asks her daughter Cathy and granddaughter Sam, both filmmakers, to make a film about it.
description2: Laura Henkel has decided she wants to end her life on her own terms, and describes why she has asked her daughter Cathy Henkel and granddaughter Sam Lara, both filmmakers, to make a film about it.

title: Anh's Brush With Fame
description: Anh Do paints some of Australia's most famous faces and captures their personalities on the canvas. The charismatic comedian, writer and Archibald Finalist delves into the inspirational stories that have shaped their lives.
description2: Anh's guest this week is household name and acclaimed performer Tina Arena, who shares her journey from child star to international success and the challenges and sacrifices that have shaped her.

title: Books That Made Us
description: Claudia Karvan embarks on a literary journey to celebrate our love of books, meet some of our most beloved and brilliant writers, and explore our Australian identity through the place, its people and the power of our stories.
description2: As an actor, Claudia Karvan knows great storytelling is all about people, great characters. What truths we can uncover about ourselves through the fictitious characters of Australian novels?

title: Australian Story
description: Putting the 'real' back into reality TV, the award-winning series with no narrator and no agendas, just authentic stories told in people's own words. For 26 years we have been telling the stories of extraordinary Australians.
description2: Emma and Richard Austin endured ten years of gruelling fertility treatment in their quest for a baby. Forced to abandon their dream, a surprise offer came from a couple facing the dilemma of managing their leftover embryos. The gift became baby Henry.

title: Stargazing Live
description: Recorded over three nights at Siding Spring Observatory (SSO) in NSW, this series immerses the audience in a celebration of the night sky, with a focus on features that are best experienced from Australian soil.
description2: Tim Minchin joins Brian Cox and Julia Zemiro on their live journey through the cosmos and Alan Duffy uses the Parkes dish to listen live for Aliens.

title: Fake Or Fortune?
description: Philip Mould and Fiona Bruce team up to investigate more thrilling cases of art world mystery and intrigue.
description2: Alice Thoday inherited a rare watercolour from her mother. If a genuine Auguste Rodin, it could be worth over 100,000 - but the trouble is, Rodin is one of the world's most faked artists.

description: Life in Australia is a battle. Shaped by the challenges of epic environments the creatures of the island continent compete for mating rights, to eat, and avoid being eaten.
description2: While forests only cover 16% of Australia's land area, they harbour a higher concentration of animal species than anywhere else on the continent.

title: Luke Warm Sex

description: This series is a crash course in great sex. Luke McGregor takes on a new challenge with the help of therapists, sex coaches & scientists, proving if someone as anxious as Luke can get better at sex, then anyone can!
description2: In an episode about giving and receiving pleasure, Luke learns the art of sensually handling your member, or someone else's. He takes a workshop in oral sex and then learns an orgasmic way to stimulate the clitoris.

description: Anh Do paints some of Australia's most famous faces and captures their personalities on the canvas. The charismatic comedian, writer and Archibald Finalist delves into the inspirational stories that have shaped their lives.

more: Host Dr. Shalin Naik, Dr. Caroline West, Dr. Sandro Demaio

description: Putting the 'real' back into reality TV, the award-winning series with no narrator and no agendas, just authentic stories told in people's own words. For 26 years we have been telling the stories of extraordinary Australians.

description2: The collapse of a major spy case involving a female double agent haunted ASIO throughout the Cold War. A new investigation of surveillance film reveals what went wrong and uncovers a possible KGB murder on Australian soil.

description: Compass explores the interface between religion and life as experienced by individuals and communities - including ordinary Australians, public leaders, religious thinkers and philosophers.

series: Old People's Home For 4 Year Olds

title: Catalyst
description: Exploring the forefront of science and technology, Catalyst brings you compelling stories taking a look at the latest in science from health and medical breakthroughs to astronomy, environment and agriculture.

description: From the makers of Kitchen Cabinet comes a ground-breaking new documentary series filmed exclusively inside the heart of Australian democracy. Join host Annabel Crabb on an all-access visit to Australia's Parliament House.
description2: Join Annabel Crabb on an all-access visit to Parliament House in Canberra. As the 45th Parliament opens with a cast of apprehensive new MPs and an unpredictable Senate, Annabel tours Australia's seat of power.

title: Catalyst
description: Exploring the forefront of science and technology, Catalyst brings you compelling stories taking a look at the latest in science from health and medical breakthroughs to astronomy, environment and agriculture.
description2: What kind of exercise should we be doing, how much do we need and how hard should push ourselves? To help us live happier healthier lives Dr Caroline West and Dr Shalin Naik uncover the latest sport science secrets from the AIS.

title: Ms Represented with Annabel Crabb
description: One hundred years after Australia elected its very first female parliamentarian, Annabel Crabb presents Ms Represented, a raw and honest account of politics from the female perspective.
description2: We track the arrival of a new wave of women into Australias Parliament in the 1970s and 80s. Annabel examines the impact women have in politics and more broadly on society, by pushing through ground-breaking legislation.

title: Songs Of Praise: Gospel Singer Of The Year 2021 Semi-Final
episode_name: Songs Of Praise: Gospel Singer Of The Year 2021 Semi-Final
description: Mark De-Lisser hosts the semi-final to find the best Gospel Singer of the Year 2021! In the first of two programmes celebrating Gospel music, five talented amateur singers take to the stage at Gorton Monastery in Manchester.
description2: Mark De-Lisser hosts the semi-final to find the best Gospel Singer of the Year 2021! In the first of two programmes celebrating Gospel music, five talented amateur singers take to the stage at Gorton Monastery in Manchester.

title: Australian Story
description: Putting the 'real' back into reality TV, the award-winning series with no narrator and no agendas, just authentic stories told in people's own words. For 26 years we have been telling the stories of extraordinary Australians.
description2: Eddie Woo first came to prominence with "Wootube" - his free YouTube maths channel. In the year since Australian Story profiled Eddie Woo, he's gone from suburban high school maths teacher to award-winning celebrity.

title: Maralinga Tjarutja
description: The Maralinga people survive aggressive colonisation, including dispossession to enable atomic testing, and through their tenacious spirit and cultural strength fight to retain their country.
description2: The Maralinga people survive aggressive colonisation, including dispossession to enable atomic testing, and through their tenacious spirit and cultural strength fight to retain their country.

title: Miriam's Deathly Adventure
description: Inimitable actress Miriam Margolyes is rather terrified of death. In this thought-provoking and entertaining documentary, she's on a mission to tackle questions of mortality and confront her fear of dying head-on.
description2: Miriam Margolyes checks into a dementia care home to see what getting old might actually look like. She meets Geoff, who visits his wife June every day following her stroke six years ago.

title: The China Century
description: The forces that have powered China's rise are rarely explored, while the lives of Chinese people barely get a mention. Beyond the headlines what do we really know about China and its 1.4 billion citizens?
description2: After 150 years of British occupation, Hong Kong was returned to China in 1997. We examine how the territory has always been defined by the contest of influence between China and the West and how that tension plays out today.

title: Love On The Spectrum
description: Seven singles take their first steps into the world of dating; this uplifting docuseries follows young adults on the autism spectrum as they explore the unpredictable world of love and relationships.
description2: Andrew wants to start a family, but has never been on a date. He heads out to a speed dating event with high hopes. Jimmy and Sharnae go on holiday together, and Jimmy has a surprise in store. (Final)

title: Australian Story
description: Putting the 'real' back into reality TV, the award-winning series with no narrator and no agendas, just authentic stories told in people's own words. For 26 years we have been telling the stories of extraordinary Australians.
description2: When the body of Mark Haines was found on the train tracks near Tamworth in 1988, police quickly dismissed any idea of foul play. But after a 5 year investigation, journalist Allan Clarke believes he may have found the truth. Walkley Award Winner for Coverage of Indigenous Affairs.

title: Chopsticks Or Fork?
description: Every country town in Australia has a Chinese restaurant and comedian and food enthusiast Jennifer Wong is on a mission to meet the people behind the wok, to find out what makes their food both Australian and Chinese.
description2: New Bo Wa Restaurant in Moree has been around since the 1970s. Ernest and Whitney Lai are the keeping up the tradition of nourishing the community with Aussie Chinese food like prawn cutlets and fried ice cream.

title: David Attenborough's Great Barrier Reef
description: Almost sixty years after his first visit to the Great Barrier Reef, David Attenborough embarks on a personal journey of discovery to understand how the Reef was created and meets the animals that call it home.
description2: David Attenborough travels to the stunning Osprey Reef where he dives in shark infested waters, in a submersible, to see the animals that use Osprey to navigate huge distances to the Barrier Reef.

title: Catalyst
description: Exploring the forefront of science and technology, Catalyst brings you compelling stories taking a look at the latest in science from health and medical breakthroughs to astronomy, environment and agriculture.
description2: Celebrate the science of beer with chef Paul West, as three teams of budding brewmasters take on the challenge to make their best homebrew. But do they have what it takes to impress our panel of international judges?

title: How To Live Younger
description: Ever wondered about the secrets to living a long, healthy and happy life? Jacinta Parsons cuts through the wellness hype and looks at the scientific 'hacks' that can help improve our lives.
description2: Scientists reveal how exercise can rewind the clock on cognitive decline, fight cancer, prevent disease, beat depression and even enhance our lives by making us smarter, more creative human beings.

title: Countdown To War
description: On Friday 1st September 1939, Germany invaded Poland and the clock started ticking. On Sunday morning, Britain had declared war. Learn about the three days that led up to the Second World War and changed the world forever.
description2: JJ Chalmers and Raksha Dave tell the dramatic story of the events of 2nd September 1939. German forces had been in Poland for more than 24 hours. War now seemed unavoidable and anxiety was building across Britain.

title: Revelation
description: Award-winning reporter Sarah Ferguson presents Revelation, a ground-breaking documentary series on the criminal priests and brothers of the Catholic Church, their crimes laid bare for the first time in their own words.
description2: The unmissable final chapter a cinematic, feature-length event, transporting you to the heart of power in the global Catholic church. This is the story of a man who has kept a shocking secret for decades. Until now. (Final)

title: War On Waste
episode_name: Series 2 Episode 1 The Battle Continues Part 1
description: Craig Reucassel returns for a 2nd series of the landmark series that sparked action across the nation. Craig targets plastic water bottles, straws, e-waste, fast furniture, food waste and the recycling crisis. #WarOnWasteAU
description2: Craig Reucassel returns for Season 2 of the series that sparked action across the nation. Craig explores our reliance on single-use plastic items such as bottles and straws that damage our waterways and marine life.

title: Fake Or Fortune?
description: Philip Mould and Fiona Bruce team up to investigate more thrilling cases of art world mystery and intrigue.
description2: The team investigate an 18th century landscape that could be a lost work by of one of the biggest names in British art, Thomas Gainsborough. Will they be able to convince an expert that it is a landscape by the great artist?

title: Capturing Cricket: Steve Waugh In India
episode_name: Capturing Cricket: Steve Waugh In India
description: Steve Waugh, the mastermind behind Australia's golden age of cricket dominance, takes us on a trip through India, exploring the rich diversity of cultures and searching for the true spirit of cricket.
description2: Steve Waugh, the mastermind behind Australia's golden age of cricket dominance, takes us on a trip through India, exploring the rich diversity of cultures and searching for the true spirit of cricket.

title: Listen Up
description: Men share deeply personal stories of how they overcame challenging health issues.
description2: Men share deeply personal stories of how they overcame challenging health issues.

title: Australian Story
description: Putting the 'real' back into reality TV, the award-winning series with no narrator and no agendas, just authentic stories told in people's own words. For 26 years we have been telling the stories of extraordinary Australians.

description: Exploring the forefront of science and technology, Catalyst brings you compelling stories taking a look at the latest in science from health and medical breakthroughs to astronomy, environment and agriculture.

title: Listen Up
description: Men share deeply personal stories of how they overcame challenging health issues.
description2: Men share deeply personal stories of how they overcame challenging health issues.

title: Who Killed Belinda Peisley? Uncovered
description: This 6-part series of digital extras takes the viewer deeper into the events of Belinda Peisley's murder case, including a closer look at the people and events surrounding Belinda at the time of her disappearance.
description2: Belinda Piesley's disappearance shook up her whole community. No body, no grieving, no funeral, her family continues to suffer today. The Families and Friends of Missing Persons Unit helps families process their pain.

description: Pools are a defining part of our national identity. Evoking deep nostalgia and childhood memories, this two-part documentary takes a look at the Australian identity through the prism of the pool.
description2: We look beneath the seductive, aqua-coloured waters of the pool to reveal its hidden history at the centre of battles over race, gender, sexuality and religion. (Final)

title: Catalyst
description: Exploring the forefront of science and technology, Catalyst brings you compelling stories taking a look at the latest in science from health and medical breakthroughs to astronomy, environment and agriculture.

title: Inside The Met
description: Go behind the scenes as the largest art museum in the Americas plans its 150th anniversary, responds to the coronavirus pandemic and calls for social justice.
description2: In spring 2019, The Met is in its glory - the coffers are full, visitor numbers are up and staff is preparing to mark the museum's 150th anniversary the following year.

title: David Attenborough's First Life
description: David Attenborough traces the origin of life, going back to the very roots of the tree of life, in search of the very first animals that moved, to the first predators that killed and the first legs that walked on land.
description2: Sir David Attenborough follows the evolution of animals from the development of mouths, exoskeletons, multi-lensed eyes and the ability to breathe on land and sea. We owe our very existence to these animals. (Final)

title: The Record
description: The plan to smash the world record for attendance at a women's sporting event depends on Australia getting through to the ICC Women's T20 World Cup final, but circumstances threaten to derail the campaign at every turn.

title: Countdown To War

description2: JJ Chalmers and Raksha Dave tell the dramatic story of the events of 3rd September 1939. At 0900 a final ultimatum was delivered to Germany, stating that they had until 1100 to respond. (Final)

title: David Attenborough's Great Barrier Reef

description2: David Attenborough travels along the Reef to understand what the next few decades may hold for this remarkable community of animals, and what is being done to try and save it. (Final)

description2: Julia's journey brings her to the glamorous island of Santorini, where she discovers how one of the Aegean's poorest islands became a playground for the rich and famous.

title: Australian Story
description: Putting the 'real' back into reality TV, the award-winning series with no narrator and no agendas, just authentic stories told in people's own words. For 26 years we have been telling the stories of extraordinary Australians.

description2: In Part 3, Craig Reucassel explores the impact that coffee cups & fast fashion have on our environment. He examines our obsession with fast fashion - an issue causing an environmental crisis globally. #WarOnWasteAU

title: Australian Story
description: Putting the 'real' back into reality TV, the award-winning series with no narrator and no agendas, just authentic stories told in people's own words. For 26 years we have been telling the stories of extraordinary Australians.

description2: Julia Hales explores people's thoughts when they face a decision about having a baby with Down Syndrome and re-examines her experience as she confronts parents' fears and celebrates the joys of living with Down Syndrome.

title: Anh's Brush With Fame
description: Anh Do paints some of Australia's most famous faces and captures their personalities on the canvas. The charismatic comedian, writer and Archibald Finalist delves into the inspirational stories that have shaped their lives.

title: Australian Story
description: Putting the 'real' back into reality TV, the award-winning series with no narrator and no agendas, just authentic stories told in people's own words. For 26 years we have been telling the stories of extraordinary Australians.

title: Australia's Ocean Odyssey: A Journey Down The East Australian Current
series: Australia's Ocean Odyssey: A Journey Down The East Australian Current
description: A landmark documentary series that takes a spectacular journey from the Great Barrier Reef down to Antarctica, revealing the ocean currents that create life on our planet, and what we can do to protect our planet's beating blue heart.
description2: As we reach the end of the East Australian Current, its remaining flow mixes into the Antarctic Circumpolar Current and the Indian Ocean. Our whales finally leave Tasmania's temperate waters on their journey to Antarctica. (Final)

title: Australian Story
description: Putting the 'real' back into reality TV, the award-winning series with no narrator and no agendas, just authentic stories told in people's own words. For 26 years we have been telling the stories of extraordinary Australians.
description2: A young woman grapples with a deadly diagnosis while waging a campaign against the biggest cancer killer of her generation.

description2: Outraged at sexual harassment in the work place and denied work at the local steelworks, a group of women band together and launch a 14 year battle against Australia's biggest company.

description2: Caro Meldrum-Hanna delves into claims of corruption and cover-ups as Exposed tries to solve the mystery of the deadly Ghost Train fire at Sydney's Luna Park. Insiders tell incredible stories that may contain the answer. (Final)

description2: There was a beautiful water world, an oasis of hope in a sterile universe but this was not Earth - this was the young Mars. Professor Brian Cox reveals that the solar system was once home to not one, but two blue planets.

title: Australian Story
description: Putting the 'real' back into reality TV, the award-winning series with no narrator and no agendas, just authentic stories told in people's own words. For 26 years we have been telling the stories of extraordinary Australians.

description2: Annabel looks at the political parties from the mid-90s to now, and what happened when - more than a century after women won the right to run for Parliament in Australia - we finally got a female Prime Minister. (Final)

title: Dubboo: Life Of A Songman

description2: Bangarra Dance Theatre joins forces with some of our most celebrated and iconic Indigenous artists in this beautiful commemorative show at Carriageworks, honouring composer and actor David Page - Bangarra's long-time songman.

description: Exploring the forefront of science and technology, Catalyst brings you compelling stories taking a look at the latest in science from health and medical breakthroughs to astronomy, environment and agriculture.

Over 8 weeks she reshapes their lives - not with medication but with lifestyle medicine, tackling chronic pain and anxiety.

title: Enslaved
description: Samuel L Jackson and a team of journalists and underwater divers explore 400 years of slavery. Each episode features a dive that brings to life the forgotten stories of some of the 2 million Africans who perished on ships.

description2: Kumi travels to Japan to deliver news to a family she hopes still exists, about a father she never really knew. Her identity is challenged as she tries to understand why she feels so at home in this intoxicating country.

description2: Australia is an island continent boasting nearly 35,000 kilometres of coastline. Humans come to the seaside to relax, but for tens of thousands of species that live and breed on our coast, it's a battleground.

title: Listen Up
description: Men share deeply personal stories of how they overcame challenging health issues.
description2: Men share deeply personal stories of how they overcame challenging health issues.

title: Australia Remastered: Nature's Great Divide
description: The hard line that separates the natural worlds of Asia from Australia is the leaping off point for amazing wild stories. The strong currents along the Wallace Line creates parallel narratives of fascinating differences.
description2: The Wallace Line divides separate worlds, where radically different animals live remarkably similar lives. This is the story of two parallel creations, and what happens when these worlds collide.

title: Ask The Doctor
description: Ask the Doctor is an innovative, fun, and exploratory factual series that addresses the state of the nation's health, the latest in medical treatments and the future of healthcare as we know it.

description: From the deep oceans in a state-of-the-art submarine on the Great Barrier Reef, to the ancient rainforests of Borneo, David Attenborough embarks on a unique natural history adventure across the globe and through time.

description2: Professor Tamara Davis meets the scientists on a quest to hunt down black holes, the journey has brought us to the cusp of an unprecedented milestone in scientific achievement - to photograph a black hole for the first time.

description2: China's return to imperial power after a century of humiliation.

description2: A behind-the-scenes look at the documentary which follows a lone penguin's battle to survive, find love and raise a family in unforgiving Antarctic conditions.

title: Australia's Ocean Odyssey: A Journey Down The East Australian Current
series: Australia's Ocean Odyssey: A Journey Down The East Australian Current

description: Hannah Gadsby is a closet art scholar. Armed with her rapier wit and a desire to pick beneath the paint, she will travel across the continent on a mission to debunk the myths of the Australian identity as defined by our art.
description2: Hannah is still searching for a more inclusive Australian identity in our art. In this episode she enters the NOW! But in post-Cronulla Australian art this Identity seems even harder to define. (Final)

description: Putting the 'real' back into reality TV, the award-winning series with no narrator and no agendas, just authentic stories told in people's own words. For 26 years we have been telling the stories of extraordinary Australians.

title: Hello Stranger
description: Hello Stranger is a contemporary snapshot of the people of Australia. We talk to people in the street, then follow one story home. It turns out that we are more complex, remarkable and much stranger than you've ever imagined.
description2: Hello Stranger asks people across Australia, "What's been a major turning point in your life?" and hears surprising answers. Then we follow Kirk Donaldson, who left home to live with his mentor, an 84-year-old magician.

title: What Is Music?

description: Why do we love a good beat? Does classical music really make you smarter? Join triple j's Linda Marigliano and composer Dan Golding as they explore the electrifying fusion of emotion and science in music.
description2: Can we make friends using music? Linda and Dan see if chanting and drum circles help them bond with strangers, and test their teamwork with synthpop band Froyo in our hardest challenge to date - building IKEA furniture.

title: The Pool

title: Waltzing The Dragon With Benjamin Law

title: Diana

description2: To mark what would have been her 60th birthday, we celebrate Diana's life. A rich tapestry of footage, photos and letters piece together her journey from shy nursery assistant to finding her voice as the Princess of Wales.

description2: A visual journey into the private life and creative legacy of Australia's most iconic artist, Brett Whiteley, told using personal letters, photographs, interwoven with reconstructions, archival interviews and rare footage.

title: What Is Music?
description: Why do we love a good beat? Does classical music really make you smarter? Join triple j's Linda Marigliano and composer Dan Golding as they explore the electrifying fusion of emotion and science in music.
description2: It's more then just pressing a button right? We give a quick history of the disc jockey in various forms, and DJ and music producer Nina Las Vegas shows us how she uses the decks.

description2: Chinese President Xi Jinping understands the greatest threat to the authoritarian state is not an invading army but the free minds of its people. This episode explores the fight for freedom of thought in China.
